{
  "text": "Cancer is one of the most frequently occurring diseases causing 8.2 million deaths in 2012 worldwide. Further breast cancer is the most often diagnosed cancer in females and the leading cause of cancer related death worldwide, with an estimated 1.7 million new cases and 522,000 deaths around the world in 2012. There has been a great advancement in cancer treatment which enhanced the patient survival and quality of life. However, cancer related deaths are continuously rising [1] [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
